---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Cookie Policy | ReloFinder.ch';
const description = 'Learn about how ReloFinder.ch uses cookies and tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience and provide better services.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="pt-20">
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Cookie Policy</h1>
          
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-0">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2025<br>
                <strong>Effective:</strong> January 1, 2025
              </p>
            </div>

            <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
            <p>
              Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites remember your preferences and provide a better user experience.
            </p>

            <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
            <p>
              ReloFinder.ch uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience, analyze website traffic, and improve our services.
            </p>

            <h3>Types of Cookies We Use:</h3>

            <h4>Essential Cookies (Always Active)</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Keep you logged in and maintain your session</li>
              <li><strong>Security:</strong> Protect against fraud and ensure secure connections</li>
              <li><strong>Form Data:</strong> Remember information you've entered in forms</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Analytics Cookies</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our website</li>
              <li><strong>Performance Tracking:</strong> Monitor website speed and functionality</li>
              <li><strong>User Behavior:</strong> Analyze which content is most helpful to users</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Functional Cookies</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> Remember your language and region settings</li>
              <li><strong>Customization:</strong> Personalize your experience based on past visits</li>
              <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> Improve form functionality and user experience</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
            <p>
              We work with trusted third-party services that may place cookies on your device:
            </p>

            <h3>Service Providers:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Website analytics and user behavior tracking</li>
              <li><strong>Cloudinary:</strong> Image optimization and delivery</li>
              <li><strong>Netlify:</strong> Website hosting and performance monitoring</li>
              <li><strong>Formspree:</strong> Contact form processing</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Cookie Consent</h2>
            <p>
              By continuing to use our website, you consent to our use of cookies as described in this policy. You can withdraw your consent at any time by adjusting your browser settings or contacting us.
            </p>

            <h3>Your Choices:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Accept all cookies for the best experience</li>
              <li>Block all cookies (may limit website functionality)</li>
              <li>Select which types of cookies to accept</li>
              <li>Delete existing cookies from your browser</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Managing Cookies</h2>
            <p>
              You can control and manage cookies through your browser settings. Here's how to manage cookies in popular browsers:
            </p>

            <h3>Browser Instructions:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
              <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
              <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
              <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Site Permissions → Cookies and Site Data</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg my-6">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-0">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Disabling certain cookies may limit your ability to use some features of our website, such as remembering your preferences or staying logged in.
              </p>
            </div>

            <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
              Different cookies have different retention periods:
            </p>

            <h3>Cookie Lifespans:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> Deleted when you close your browser</li>
              <li><strong>Persistent Cookies:</strong> Remain for a set period (typically 1-2 years)</li>
              <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> 26 months (Google Analytics standard)</li>
              <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> 1 year or until you clear them</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>7. Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable laws. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated policy on this page.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
              If you have questions about our use of cookies or this Cookie Policy, please contact us:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@relofinder.ch">privacy@relofinder.ch</a></li>
              <li><strong>Subject:</strong> "Cookie Policy Inquiry"</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>9. Related Policies</h2>
            <p>
              For more information about how we handle your personal data, please see our:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
              <li><a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout> 